description: An information artifact is, loosely, a dependent continuant or its bearer that is created as the result of one or more intentional processes.  Examples: uniprot, the english language, the contents of this document or a printout of it, the temperature measurements from a weather balloon.  For more information, see the project home page at [link](https://github.com/information-artifact-ontology/IAO).
name: Information Artifact Ontology (IAO)
